cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM 

This paper discusses the development of new spectrum regulation policies for wireless communication systems, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference management protocols, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of cognitive MAC protocols is related to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) due to the need for efficient and reliable transmission of multimedia data.
